description:
The Bible is God’s message; it is His word given to humanity in our language through men who were inspired and “moved by the Holy Spirit” (2 Peter 1:21). 

As Seventh-day Adventists, the Scriptures are the very foundation upon which we base all of our beliefs. Hence, the very first fundamental belief of the Church pertains to our belief in the truth and inspiration of the Holy Scriptures. 

Listen to Pastor Ted Wilson’s message as he shows how Jesus is woven throughout the entire Bible because the Scriptures are a perfect representation of Him and His gospel plan of salvation. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xJeAv9lKHNc&list=PL-k2Gb-DBYo_ANrUJhHN2_4bSlMDTjuqQ&index=96

—---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The Seventh-day Adventist Church has been an established denomination since 1863. It is a global Christian family with over 21 million members who hold the Bible as the ultimate authority. We are Christians who promise to help people understand the Bible to find freedom, healing, and hope in Jesus.

Want to learn more about the Seventh-day Adventist Church? 
Visit our website at: https://www.adventist.org/ 

Click the notification bell so that you never miss a new video!
